Job Description


Ubisoft IT is looking for an experienced and dedicated 
IT Project Manager
 to join our growing team: Security and Risk Management (SRM). You will support our teams in establishing and leading enterprise-wide, cross-functional strategic security initiatives. Your focus on the medium term will be to plan, orchestrate and deliver projects prioritized from the security portfolio of initiatives. We also support other global security programs such as Cloud security, DevSecOps and Vulnerability Management.


Responsibilities



Identify, challenge and consolidate the needs of stakeholders to define and maintain project objectives and also key results, scope, metrics, and validate project deliverables;

Manage project activities to meet project scope, budget and schedule and elicit standard project management artefacts as needed, track KPIs and escalate variances as necessary to the appropriate stakeholders;

Assist team leads and subject matter experts (SMEs) in identifying and planning short and long term project priorities as well as requirements in JIRA backlog;

Develop communication plans and interfaces with multiple stakeholders to execute responsibilities;

Contribute to the elaboration of budget forecasts for fiscal year budget planning;

Act as a coach for team members on project management and agile best practices, providing leadership and expertise on project management and agile standards;

Seek out opportunities to improve Ubisoft’s SRM business management activities.




Qualifications



Significant experience in project management and thorough mastery of both waterfall and agile (scrum and Kanban) practices;

Ability to communicate at all levels with clarity and precision, both written and verbally;

Proven ability to quickly earn the trust of key stakeholders, motivate teams, and make the messages accessible;

Sound business and technical acumen; experienced in stakeholder management;

Experience building and leveraging wide professional networks to advance team goals;

Have a customer centric approach, constantly seeks, and appropriately; incorporates customer feedback to refine scope throughout the project life cycle.




