THE ORGANIZATION 




Founded in 2009, OBIO® is a not-for-profit, membership-based innovation organization engaged in strategy, programming, policy development and advocacy to further the commercialization of human health technologies positioning Canada as a leader in the international marketplace. OBIO advances this goal through collaborative partnerships with industry, the investment community, academia, the health system and government. 




THE OPPORTUNITY 




This is an exciting marketing and communications role that is entrepreneurial and hands-on. It is an opportunity for you to “make your mark” working for a focused organization that is at the forefront of Canadian health science working with companies hands-on to deliver programs that are driven by their needs. It’s the only organization that does this and you are impacting healthcare and lives through the success of these companies. The culture is fast paced, creative, professional and team oriented. 




This is an exciting growth role due to its breadth of responsibilities and special projects. It is not a “status quo” organization. It is agile and innovative as it is small. You can learn and grow your skill sets. You can make a direct impact on improving people’s lives! 




THE POSITION 




Reporting to the Manager, Marketing &amp; Events, the Associate, Marketing &amp; Communications will support organizational marketing and communications, both external and internal, related to all OBIO activities, including but not limited to corporate events, OBIO programming and workshops, OBIO’s social media presence, and stakeholder outreach. This position is instrumental in planning, developing and administering OBIO events – conferences, workshops, symposia – that support the commercial development of the biotechnology industry in Ontario. Tasks are extremely varied and depend on the particulars of the event, project or channel. 




KEY RESPONSIBILITIES




•       Manages OBIO social media channels, including drafting, creating visuals, posting and reporting;

•       Develops external marketing and communications materials, including communications plans, newsletters, marketing materials and reports, while ensuring consistency of the OBIO brand; 

•       Plays a key role in organizing, marketing and executing OBIO events, including conferences, workshops and networking events, and other related events 

•       Maintains OBIO website event calendars, webinars and other organizational communications; and 

•       Works collaboratively with the entire OBIO Team 

 

KEY QUALIFICATIONS 




The ideal candidate will bring the following skills and experiences: 

•       Undergraduate degree (experience in sciences/business/marketing is an asset);

•       Interest in/understanding of biotechnology, science, health and technology-based businesses;; 

•       Knowledge of digital media environment: major social media platforms and website management; 

•       Comfortable creating visuals and graphics; and

•       Strong communications and organizational skills and the ability to manage competing priorities. 




EXPERIENCE PREFERRED 




•       Minimum of 2 to 3 years experience in marketing and communications, including the development of marketing and communications plans ideally from the healthcare industry sector; 

•       Previous experience in event planning including project management and day-of execution; 

•       Previous experience in health science industry/start-up work environment is an asset; 

•       Developing digital communications and outreach materials, including writing and preparing online newsletters, writing web content and managing a social media presence; 

•       Experience with digital photography, photo editing, video editing, and graphic and web design is an asset. 

•       Experience using file management systems and CRM platforms




SKILLS REQUIRED 




•       Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written; 

•       Excellent organizational skills; 

•       Ability to work as part of a team structure; 

•       Strong project management skills combined with a high level of accountability; 

•       Working knowledge of SME and/or not-for-profit business issues desirable; 

•       Social media experience and savvy; and 

•       Proficient with Microsoft Office suite of applications and related business software. 




KEY ATTRIBUTES 




•       Must possess unquestionable personal and professional integrity; 

•       Dynamic team player; 

•       Excellent interpersonal skills &amp; ability to work collaboratively; 

•       Results oriented: able to manage self, influence others and utilize available resources to achieve ambitious goals; 

•       Self-motivated and able to thrive under pressure in a flexible and changing working environment; 

•       “Can do” attitude combined with strong attention to detail and a high level of accuracy and commitment to timelines; 

•       Sets high standards for themselves and in their work; 

•       Respect for maintaining confidentiality; and 

•       Entrepreneurial big thinker mind set and work ethic with a strong business acumen. 





EDUCATION 





Undergraduate degree (experience in sciences/business is an asset). 




OBIO welcomes and encourages applications from people with disabilities. Accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process.

