We are currently recruiting for 
a Product Line Manager for our RF &amp; Optical products
 to join our growing team in Whitby, ON. ATX Networks offers an outstanding work environment and a competitive compensation package. 




Reporting to the VP, Access Network Products, the 
Product Line Manager (PLM)
 is responsible for driving the product direction of various ATX’s RF &amp; Optical products by defining product road maps, strategy, and development opportunities. This includes managing products throughout the Product Lifecycle, gathering and prioritizing product and customer requirements, defining the product vision, and working closely with Engineering to deliver market-leading products. It also includes working with Sales, Marketing and Support to ensure revenue and customer satisfaction goals are met. The Product Line Manager’s job also includes ensuring that the product and marketing efforts support the company’s overall strategy and goals. It is expected the successful candidate for the role possesses relevant product lifecycle, industry and market expertise to translate ATX product and market strategy into financial results. Fundamentally, a PLM will take ownership of the success and failures of a specific set of products from inception through to End of Life.




We seek talented, enthusiastic, innovative and flexible individuals, who are looking for a challenging and rewarding career. We host a positive, modern, casual environment.





RESPONSIBLITIES:







Develop and deliver New Product Introduction documents (NPI) which include:

Analysis of Market Size and Competition

High level product definition &amp; goal

Required resources (personnel, infrastructure, and CAPEX)

Estimated development and deployment timeline

Product pricing and cost targets

Develop and deliver Product Requirements Documents (PRDs) which include:

Product overview and use cases

Requirements, including:

functional, physical, environment, technical

security, network, platform, integration, client

support, interoperability

Assumptions, Constraints, Dependencies

Maintain NPI schedule updates &amp; milestones

Evaluation plan and performance metrics

Ensure new parts are defined accurately in the ATX system

Manage End-of-Life, Manufacturing Discontinuance, End of Service plans

Work with external third parties to assess partnerships and licensing opportunities;

Be an expert with respect to the competition; conduct competitive analysis and market research to guide product planning

Develop the core positioning and messaging for the product;

Perform product demos and training to customers and internal ATX staff;

Represent ATX at customer briefings, technology, and partner forums;

Recommend pricing to meet revenue and profitability goals;

Work in concert with Engineering to develop product road maps;

Support Marketing in developing sales tools, whitepapers and collateral;

Propose and track to an overall budget to ensure success;

Act as a leader within the company;

Prepare weekly status reports in the form of PowerPoint presentations, and;

Execute all responsibilities in an ethical manner consistent with statutory requirements and company policies.









QUALIFICATIONS: 








A Bachelor’s degree and 5+ years relevant experience in the Cable industry MSO and/or Vendor, with a specific focus on RF and Optical products

MSO technical operations management or corporate engineering experience is a plus.

Strong ability to support sales, listen to customer requirements and problems and provide guidance to position existing products or take away and analyze those requirements towards developing a business case for new products and features.

A solid technical understanding of translating individual product specification to end-to-end System design and performance specifications.

Familiarity with RF and optical test measurement techniques.

Experience and understanding DOCSIS 3.1 &amp; 4.0 specifications and relation to stated products is a plus.

Demonstrated success defining and launching leading-edge products;

Excellent written and verbal communication skills;

Proven ability to influence cross-functional teams without formal authority;

Must be able to travel 25% of the time;

Interpersonal skills, supporting the ability to work with diverse personalities, build effective relationships and interact appropriately and effectively at all levels of the organization and externally;

Superior communication skills, the ability to communicate inside and outside the organization, to persuade, negotiate and/or instruct both orally and in writing;

Results oriented with the ability to recognize, balance and support the organization’s preferences, other business considerations and priorities;

Technology &amp; computer skills for reporting, communications and presentations;

Demonstrates strong business acumen and communications expertise in dealing with ATX suppliers, senior level executives and investors; 

Strong analytical, numerical, and reasoning abilities.
